UNITED STATES of America ex rel. CHIN MING GEE, Relator-Appellant, v. Edward CORSI, Commissioner of Immigration, New York, N. Y., Respondent-Appellee. No. 88. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Oct. 17, 1932. Griffiths & Content, of New York City, for appellant. George Z. Medalie, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Maurice DcKoven, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for respondent.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed on the authority of U. S. ex rel. Fong On v. Day (C. C. A.) 54 F.(2d) 990.
